{{Infobox language |name=Budu Dogon |nativename=Bunɔɡɛ |region=[[Mali]] |speakers=1,000 |date=2005 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Dogon languages|Dogon]] |fam3=West |iso3=dgb |glotto=buno1241 |glottorefname=Bunoge Dogon }} '''Budu Dogon''' or '''''Bunoge''''', also known as '''Korandabo''', is a recently discovered [[Dogon language]] spoken in [[Mali]]. It was first reported online.[https://web.archive.org/web/20130615111624/http://www.rogerblench.info/Language/Niger-Congo/Dogon/Dogon%20page.htm] The plural suffix on nouns is closest to [[Kolum so]], suggesting it should be classified as a West Dogon language.
The people call themselves ''Budu'', and [[Tommo so|Tɔmmɔ-sɔ]] speakers call the language ''Budu-sɔ''. It has also been called ''Budu-Tagu'', the name of the principal Budu village.
