'''IIIMF''' ('''Internet/Intranet Input Method Framework''') is the default [[input method]] framework for Chinese (Simplified and Traditional), Japanese and Korean on old [[Fedora (operating system)|Fedora]] Linux systems.<ref>http://docs.fedoraproject.org/release-notes/fc2/x86/</ref>  Since Fedora Core 5, ''[[Smart Common Input Method|SCIM]]'' has been selected as the default input method framework instead.  Developed by Hideki Hiura, it supports [[Unicode]] and allows multiple language engines to run at the same time.<ref>http://www.unifont.org/iuc27/html/img34.html</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jp.redhat.com/magazine/NO3/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-03-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090915013829/http://www.jp.redhat.com/magazine/NO3/ |archivedate=2009-09-15 |df= }}</ref>

