{{Expand Spanish|Julio César Castro|date=February 2016}} '''Julio César Castro''', also known as '''Juceca''' ([[Montevideo]], 6 May 1928 – Ib., 11 September 2003) was a [[Uruguay]]an [[Humour|comedian]], narrator, [[actor]] and [[Playwright|dramatist]]. He was mainly known by his character Don Verídico,<ref>[http://buenosairesherald.com/article/186688/in-memory-of-a-man-whose-name-was-a-book In memory of a man whose name was a book]</ref> with which he developed a particular type of [[wikt:absurd|absurd]] humour tied to the rural world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emisoradelsur.com.uy/innovaportal/v/31108/30/mecweb/don-veridico-en-su-propia-voz?parentid%3D28549 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-12-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222113342/http://www.emisoradelsur.com.uy/innovaportal/v/31108/30/mecweb/don-veridico-en-su-propia-voz?parentid=28549 |archivedate=2015-12-22 |df= }}</ref>
