The '''Mean Streak''' is a type of [[Paint marker#Solidified paint pens|marker]] made by [[Sanford (writing products)|Sanford]], but can also refer to a variety of solidified paint marking sticks. This marker is a semi-solidified stick of oil-based paint in a twist tube which makes marks on many types of surfaces, including metal, wood, plastics, and paper, making it a popular [[graffiti]] instrument.<ref name="FreitagMuhs2003">{{cite book|author1=Sabine Freitag|author2=Rudolf Muhs|title=Exiles From European Revolutions: Refugees in Mid-Victorian England|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_RPdCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA135|date=15 July 2003|publisher=Berghahn Books|isbn=978-1-78238-979-8|pages=135}}</ref> It leaves a mark similar to a crayon or chalk. They come in a variety of colors; the original colors were blue, red and yellow.
